As of today, it has not been proven with certainty that any drug is suitable for treating the existing infection caused by ebola, even though there is an experimental vaccine that seems to be able to reduce the mortality caused by that disease.
ZMapp, a combination of antibodies, had a promising result in the field at the beginning, but formal studies showed that it was less beneficial than expected to prevent death.
In the PALM trial, the function of ZMapp was control, i.e., that the scientists used it as a base and compared it with the other three treatments.
USA Gymnastics supports the statement of the United States Olympic & Paralympic Committee and recognizes that it is imperative that the Olympic and Paralympic family foster a safe environment for all of our athletes.
We agree with the USOC's statement that the interests of athletes, clubs and their sports can be better served if we move forward with significant changes within our organization, rather than the withdrawal of accreditation.
USA Gymnastics supports an independent investigation that can clarify how the abuse that the survivors of Larry Nassar described with such courage could have gone on for so long without being seen and accepts any necessary and appropriate changes.
The goal of USA Gymnastics and USOC is the same: to ensure that gymnastics and other sports are as safe as possible for athletes to pursue their dreams in a protected, positive and enhanced environment.
During the 1960s, Brzezinski worked for John F. Kennedy in the position of advisor and, later, for the government of Lyndon B. Johnson.
Advised Carter on foreign policy in the 1976 elections. Later, worked as an ASN between 1977 and 1981, after Henry Kissinger.
As national security advisor, he assisted Carter in the diplomatic management of international affairs, such as the Camp David Accords of 1978, the normalization of relations between the United States and China in the late 1970s, the Iranian Revolution of 1979, which led to a hostage crisis in Iran, and the Soviet invasion of Afghanistan in 1979.
