It was discovered that the sun was governed by the same basic principles as other stars: the only factors that drove its activity within the solar system were its luminosity and its rotation.
The intensity of the light and the rotation are combined to calculate the Rossby number of a star, linked to the flow of plasma.
The smaller the number of Rossby, the smaller the activity of the star in relation to its magnetic inversions.
