The 802.11n standard works on both 2.4Ghz and 5.0Ghz frequencies.
This will make possible its compatibility with previous versions of 802.11a, 802.11b and 802.11g, insofar as the base station has dual radios.
The speeds of the 802.11n standard are much higher than those achieved by those that preceded it, with a theoretical maximum of 600 Mbps.
